700043f-b.title: Bronx: 135th Street (East) - Willis Avenue
700043f-b.text:
(1)
East 135th Street, west from (No. 351) a point between Willis and Alexander Aves. (the Third Avenue Elevated Structure), showing the cleared area extending to East 134th Street, which is being constructed into the Westerly approach to the Triborough Bridge.
July 29, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing also East 134th Street (left).
November 14, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

700044f-a.title: Bronx: 135th Street (East) - Willis Avenue
700044f-a.text:
369 to 343 (right to left) East 135th Street, north side, between Willis and Alexander Aves. (directly west of the Third Ave. Elevated structure). Also shown is part of the clearance between East 134th and 135th Streets which will be part of the approach to
the Triborough Bridge.
November 14, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

700045f-a.title: Bronx: 135th Street (East) - Willis Avenue
700045f-a.text:

383 to 371 (rimht to left), East 135th Street, north side (buildingw thereon), at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Willis Ave. The view is northwestward from East 134th Street across the cleared area which will be constructed into an approach to the Triborough Bridge. On the
extreme left is the Third Ave. Elevated structure.

P. L. Sperr.

700046f-a.title: Bronx: 135th Street (East) - Willis Avenue
700046f-a.text:
(1)
383 to 371 (right to left), East 135th Street (buildings thereon), north side, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Willis Ave. Extending from East 135th to East 134th Streets (foreground), is a clearance created by the demolition of buildings that occupied the site, to facilitate the construotion of an approach to the Triborough Bridge.
May 7, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, at a later date. On the left is the Third Ave. Elevated
structure.
November 14, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

700055f-b.title: Bronx: 135th Street (East) - Willis Avenue
700055f-b.text:
(1)
East 135th Street (extreme left), south side, east from Willis Ave., showing the extensive cleared area between East 135th and East 134th (extreme right) Streets which is being constructed into an approach to the Triborough Bridge. Several hundred buildings formerly
occupied this area.
July 29, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, as seen from (No. 446) a point farther east; between
Willis Ave. and Brown Place.
July 29, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
